; Regression test for issue #2005: balance assignments with --permissive.
;
; When a posting uses the balance assignment syntax with no explicit amount
; (e.g., Assets:Checking =$12345), --permissive does not change the balance
; assignment semantics.  The assignment computes the amount needed to bring
; the account to the target balance.  If that amount causes the transaction
; not to balance, the error is reported normally — --permissive only
; suppresses balance ASSERTION errors, not balance assignment computation.

2021/02/14 Test transaction
  Liabilities:Visa  $3141
  Assets:Checking  =$12345

test bal --permissive -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 12:
While balancing transaction from "$FILE", lines 10-12:
> 2021/02/14 Test transaction
>   Liabilities:Visa  $3141
>   Assets:Checking  =$12345
Unbalanced remainder is:
              $15486
Amount to balance against:
              $15486
Error: Transaction does not balance
end test
